{"ts":"2026-06-11T06:31:44Z","verb":"GH","url":"issue create --repo kim-em/lean-zip --title feat: prove repairBl lands on a complete code (blKraft = 2^maxBits) \u2014 histogram core of #2536 --label agent-plan,feature --body **Proof-quality ratchet (Wave 2b) \u2014 the hard histogram-level core of `computeCodeLengths_complete` (#2536). Proof-only: `Zip/Spec/HuffmanEncode.lean` (+ possibly a small `cappedBlCount` refactor to WF recursion). No behavior change.**\n\n### Goal\n\nProve the zlib `gen_bitlen` redistribution lands *exactly* on a complete code at the histogram level:\n\n```\ntheorem repairBl_complete (bl : Array Nat) (maxBits : Nat) (hmb : maxBits > 0)\n    (... invariant hyps ...) :\n    blKraft (repairBl bl (blKraft bl maxBits - 2 ^ maxBits) maxBits) maxBits = 2 ^ maxBits\n```\n\ni.e. running `repairBl` with `excess = blKraft bl maxBits \u2212 2^maxBits` ends with `blKraft = 2^maxBits`.\n\n### Why this is the crux\n\nEach repair step does `bl[bits]\u22121`, `bl[bits+1]+=2`, `bl[maxBits]\u22121`, which lowers `blKraft` by **exactly 1** \u2014 *provided* the step is well-defined: `bits = findBelow bl (maxBits\u22121) > 0` and `bl[maxBits] \u2265 1` (else the Nat `\u22121`s are no-ops and the count/Kraft accounting breaks). Neither is guaranteed by `excess > 0` alone \u2014 there are histograms (e.g. `bl[1]=3, maxBits=2`) that are over-subscribed with `bl[maxBits]=0`. Well-definedness needs the **Kraft-prefix feasibility invariant** that a capped real binary tree satisfies but an arbitrary histogram does not.\n\n### Suggested decomposition (the next agent may sub-split further)\n\n1. **Per-step arithmetic** (`blKraft` under three sequential `set!`s): a `blKraft`/`set!` increment lemma analogous to `kraftSumFrom_incr` in `Zip/Spec/HuffmanKraft.lean`, giving \"one step lowers `blKraft` by exactly 1\" under `1 \u2264 bits \u2264 maxBits\u22121`, `bl[bits] \u2265 1`, `bl[maxBits] \u2265 1`. Mind the `bits+1 = maxBits` aliasing case (the `+2` and `\u22121` compose on one cell \u2014 see the `repairBl` docstring).\n2. **Loop invariant** through `repairBl` (induction on `excess`): conservation (`blKraft bl maxBits = 2^maxBits + excess_remaining`) **+** prefix feasibility (`\u03a3_{l=1}^{b} bl[l]\u00b72^(b\u2212l) \u2264 2^b` for `1 \u2264 b < maxBits`) **+** leaf-count bound (`blCountSum bl maxBits \u2264 2^maxBits`, `blCountSum` is already in the file). From these: while over-subscribed, `findBelow > 0` (else all leaves at `maxBits`, so `blKraft = blCountSum \u2264 2^maxBits`, contradiction) and `bl[maxBits] \u2265 1`, and the invariant is preserved by a step.\n3. **Establish the invariant for `cappedBlCount`**: relate the capped histogram to the source tree's prefix Kraft sums. NOTE: `cappedBlCount` is written as `Id.run do ... for p in depths do ...` \u2014 a `forIn` loop whose `loop\u271d` cannot be unfolded (see CLAUDE.md \"Opaque loop functions\"). Expect to refactor `cappedBlCount` to well-founded recursion first, then prove a binary-tree prefix-Kraft lemma (every prefix `\u03a3_{l\u2264b} count[l]\u00b72^(b\u2212l) \u2264 2^b`, with equality only past max depth). `BuildTree.kraft_eq` (full-tree Kraft = `2^(D\u2212d)`) is the starting point.\n\n### Already landed (build on these \u2014 do not redo)\n\nIn `Zip/Spec/HuffmanEncode.lean`: `expandBl_kraft` (`kraftSum (expandBl bl) = blKraft bl`), `kraftSum_perm`, `blCountSum` + `expandBl_length`, and the per-length lemmas `kraftSum_cons/_replicate/_flatMap_replicate`. `Zip/Spec/HuffmanKraft.lean` has the `ncRec`/`kraftSumFrom`/`kraftSumFrom_incr`/`ncRec_bound` machinery \u2014 the prefix-feasibility analogue lives there and `kraftSumFrom_incr` is the template for step 1.\n\n### Context\n\nThis permanently rules out the zlib-rejected-incomplete-code bug class D-20 fixed, independent of tests. Feeds #2536's bridge half (its sibling sub-issue), which turns this histogram equality into the per-symbol `computeCodeLengths_complete` statement.\n\n### Verification\n\n`lake build && lake exe test` green; `grep -rc sorry Zip/` = 0; no `native_decide`.\n","status":0,"ms":1197,"cache_hit":false,"caller":"coordination.py:cmd_plan:718","bucket":"core","transport":"gh"}
