{"ts":"2026-06-11T06:32:05Z","verb":"GH","url":"issue create --repo kim-em/lean-zip --title feat: bridge repairBl completeness to computeCodeLengths_complete (kraftSum = 2^maxBits) \u2014 #2536 bridge half --label agent-plan,feature,blocked --body **Proof-quality ratchet (Wave 2b) \u2014 the bridge half of `computeCodeLengths_complete` (#2536). Proof-only: `Zip/Spec/HuffmanEncode.lean`. No behavior change.**\n\ndepends-on: #2543\n\n### Goal\n\nTurn the histogram-level Kraft equality (`blKraft (repaired bl) maxBits = 2^maxBits`, delivered by #2543) into the per-symbol completeness statement and the deliverables in #2536:\n\n1. `computeCodeLengths_complete`: for `freqs` with \u2265 2 distinct nonzero-frequency symbols, all `< numSymbols`, with `numSymbols \u2264 2^maxBits`,\n   ```\n   kraftSum ((computeCodeLengths freqs numSymbols maxBits).filter (\u00b7 != 0)) maxBits = 2 ^ maxBits\n   ```\n   (mirror the shape of `computeCodeLengths_valid`, which proves the `\u2264` half.)\n2. Corollary: `fixKraftList` is the identity on the multi-symbol `computeCodeLengths` output (its overflow branch is proven-dead), stated as a simp-able equation if convenient.\n3. Document the 1-symbol boundary explicitly in the hypothesis (RFC 1951 known exception \u2014 `computeCodeLengths` short-circuits to length 1, `kraftSum = 2^(maxBits\u22121) \u2260 2^maxBits`).\n\n### Proof path (the pieces are mostly landed)\n\nThe multi-symbol `computeCodeLengths` output, filtered nonzero, is a **permutation of `expandBl bl`** (the repaired histogram's length multiset): `limitedPairs` zips the frequency-sorted distinct symbols with `expandBl bl ++ padding`, and `|symsByFreq| = nonzero.length = blCountSum bl maxBits = (expandBl bl).length` (via `expandBl_length` + `repairBl` preserving `blCountSum` \u2014 the latter falls out of #2543's loop invariant), so the padding is unused. Then:\n\n```\nkraftSum (filter nonzero output) = kraftSum (expandBl bl)   -- kraftSum_perm (landed)\n                                 = blKraft bl               -- expandBl_kraft (landed)\n                                 = 2^maxBits                -- #2543\n```\n\nRemaining work is the permutation argument over `assignLengths (symsByFreq.zip ...) numSymbols`: filtering the foldl-of-`set` result at *distinct, in-range* symbol positions yields exactly the multiset of assigned lengths. Needs symbol distinctness (from `freqs`) and `< numSymbols`. Look at `assignLengths_pos` / `foldl_set_pos_or_exists` for the existing set-fold reasoning style.\n\n### Already landed (build on these \u2014 do not redo)\n\n`Zip/Spec/HuffmanEncode.lean`: `kraftSum_perm`, `expandBl_kraft`, `expandBl_length`, `blCountSum`, `limitedPairs_map_fst`, `limitedPairs_covers`, `limitedPairs_mem_range`. The `assignLengths` length/bound/pos lemmas are all present.\n\n### Context\n\nCompletes #2536's gold-standard characterizing property: the encoder hot path provably cannot regress into incomplete (zlib-rejected) codes, independent of tests.\n\n### Verification\n\n`lake build && lake exe test` green; `grep -rc sorry Zip/` = 0; no `native_decide`; theorem uses the \u2265 2-symbol hypothesis explicitly.\n","status":0,"ms":1085,"cache_hit":false,"caller":"coordination.py:cmd_plan:718","bucket":"core","transport":"gh"}
